the Collapse is an event {
    date year -312, era "Station Reckoning"
    type cataclysm

    """
    The event that severed contact between the colony network and
    Earth. Whether Earth was destroyed, cut off, or simply stopped
    responding is unknown. The drift lanes destabilized and dozens
    of stations were lost.
    """
}

the Founding of the Mandate is an event {
    date year 0, era "Station Reckoning"
    type political
    involving [the Helios Mandate, the Meridian Hub]

    """
    In the chaos after the Collapse, the administrators of Meridian
    Hub declared emergency authority over the surviving stations.
    Year zero of Station Reckoning.
    """
}

the First Cascade Expansion is an event {
    date year 84, era "Station Reckoning"
    type supernatural
    involving [the Hollows]

    """
    The Cascade zone doubled in size over a three-day period,
    swallowing two outlying stations. Survivors described reality
    folding in on itself before their evacuation ships cleared
    the boundary.
    """
}

the Freerunner Secession is an event {
    date year 197, era "Station Reckoning"
    type political
    involving [the Freerunner Collective, the Helios Mandate]

    """
    Salvage crews refused to pay the Mandate's new 40% recovery
    tax and formally organized as the Freerunner Collective.
    The Mandate lacks the fleet strength to enforce compliance
    beyond the Meridian Hub's immediate vicinity.
    """
}

the Ghost of Io Discovery is an event {
    date year 301, month 6, day 14, era "Station Reckoning"
    type discovery
    involving [Captain Rynn Vasik, the Ghost of Io, the Hollows]

    """
    Captain Vasik's crew discovered the derelict freighter Ghost
    of Io at the Hollows boundary. The ship's logs were corrupted
    but fragments suggest it had been drifting for centuries â€”
    longer than the Collapse itself.
    """
}

the Anchor Seven Signal is an event {
    date year 305, month 2, era "Station Reckoning"
    type discovery
    involving [Dr Asha Lien, Anchor Point Seven, the Singing Frequency]

    """
    Dr Lien's research team first isolated the Singing Frequency
    and traced it to Anchor Point Seven. Her preliminary report
    to the Mandate was classified immediately.
    """
}
